<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-10-21T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-10-21T11:00:00-05:00" n="232" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d232">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">340.1115A/1553: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Germany</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Morris</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-10-21T18:00:00+02:00">October 21, 1940—6 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received October 21—4:27 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>4393. My 4339, October 16, 5 p.m.<note n="71" xml:id="d232fn71">Not
                                    printed.</note> The Foreign Office this afternoon orally and it
                                was emphasized “informally and unofficially” informed the Embassy
                                that because of the battle situation (<hi rend="italic">Kampflage</hi>) in the area of operations around the British
                                Isles it was impossible to give any sort of assurance of
                                safe-conduct for an American vessel to proceed to and return from a
                                western or southern Irish port for the repatriation of American
                                citizens from the British Isles.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>